frameDefinitions: A Payer gives up (or potentially gives up) the use of an Asset (generally money) in order to achieve an Intended_event.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
Geography as defined by its use.
An Agent, by virtue of strength or forcefulness, controls, rules, or strongly influences some Patient in some Situation.
A Person is in a state of prosperity and/or renown after some period of development or hardship in an Endeavor.
A Person or Institution is being described in terms of their wealthiness, in other words the amount of money in their possession.
frameExamples: It 'll <t>cost</t> Sandra's parents fifty grand a year for her to attend that school.
You must land in the next <t><fex name='Locale'>airfield</fex></t>, as this one is currently having difficulties.
The fireballing righthander looked poised to <t>dominate</t> the Yankees yet again, striking out seven straight batters during one stretch
listRoleDefinitions: The role <fen>Goods</fen> is the item(s) whose price is being assessed.  <fen>Goods</fen> is usually an External Argument:
The person whose <fen>Asset</fen> is given up in order to achieve an <fen>Intended_event</fen>.  This role is often expressed as INI.
The price of or payment made for the Goods.
The event that the <fen>Payer</fen> brings about by deploying the <fen>Asset</fen>.
The time when a transaction takes place.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
A stable bounded area.  It is typically the designation of the nouns of Locale-derived frames.
The activity that is carried out in the <fen>Locale</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> controls the Patient by being forceful and possibly aggressive.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is trying to gain control of a situation, but ends up being subject to the control and influence of the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The time when the domination takes place.
The place where the domination occurs.
A sentient being or group of beings that is prosperous or well known after being involved in some <fen>Endeavor</fen>.
An event that the <fen>Person</fen> is involved in which leads to their state of prosperity or renown.
The time when the <fen>Entity</fen> is determined to be successful.
The individual or individuals whose wealthiness is being described.
A group which has (or lacks) possession of some resource.
listRoleExamples: A holiday in Europe is very expensive <fex>for me</fex>.
No, they've got a special on; it's really cheap there <fex>on Tuesdays</fex>
The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
There used to be a carnival every summer in that <fex><t>city</t></fex>.
The Campus <fex>Microscopy and Imaging</fex> Facility (CMIF) serves a wide range of faculty staff and students of The Ohio State University .
Their role models might have dominated women <fex>in the past</fex>; they may not have understood the concept of equality.
Women tend to dominatemen <fex>at home and at Church</fex>.
<fex>He</fex> became a success at the age of 25.
Looking back, I had a very successful <fex>career</fex>.
After 20 years of hard work, he finally made it as an artist <fex>in '84</fex>.
<fex>Pat and Kim</fex> are completely broke at the moment.
